This memorandum, addressed to the Secretary of State, delegates certain authorities under the Foreign Assistance Act of 1961 to provide assistance to Ukraine. The delegated authorities include the determination of whether it is important to the security interests of the United States to provide up to $150 million in assistance without regard to any provision of law, as well as the authority to direct the drawdown of up to $150 million in defense articles and services, military education, and training for Ukraine. The memorandum is signed by President Joseph R. Biden Jr.